1. HUNT OBJECT (ROOT)
A Hunt is a portable, self‑contained content unit.
Hunt {
  id: string (required)
  title: string (required)
  description: string (optional)
  thumbnail: string (optional)
  difficulty: "Easy" | "Medium" | "Hard" | string (optional)
  tags: string[] (optional)

  version: string (required)
  creator: string (optional)

  startNodeId: string (required)
  nodes: Node[] (required)
  items: Item[] (optional)

  scoring: ScoringConfig (optional)
  statePersistence: "session" | "persistent" (optional)
}

Rules
id must be unique across all hunts.
nodes[] must contain startNodeId.
No circular references unless explicitly intended.
All referenced items must exist in items[].

2. NODE OBJECT
Nodes define the playable flow.
Node {
  id: string (required)
  type: string (required)

  title: string (optional)
  body: string (optional)

  nextNodeId: string | null (optional)
  failNodeId: string | null (optional)

  requires: string[] (optional)
  conditions: Condition[] (optional)

  timerSeconds: number | null (optional)

  puzzle: PuzzleData (optional)
  wordPuzzle: WordPuzzleData (optional)
  gemChoices: GemChoice[] (optional)

  ui: NodeUI (optional)
}

Rules
type must match an engine‑supported node type.
If nextNodeId is provided, it must reference a valid node.
If failNodeId is provided, it must reference a valid node.
requires must reference valid item IDs.
conditions must be valid condition objects.

3. ITEM OBJECT
Items represent keys, collectibles, or inventory objects.
Item {
  id: string (required)
  name: string (required)
  icon: string (optional)
  rarity: "common" | "rare" | "epic" | "legendary" | string (optional)
  description: string (optional)
}

Rules
Item IDs must be unique.
Items referenced in nodes must exist here.

4. SCORING CONFIG
Defines how the ScoreEngine calculates totals.
ScoringConfig {
  enabled: boolean (required)
  maxTimeBonus: number (optional)

  weights: {
    time: number (optional)
    itemCommon: number (optional)
    itemRare: number (optional)
    itemEpic: number (optional)
    itemLegendary: number (optional)
  }
}

Rules
If enabled = false, engine ignores scoring.
Missing weights default to engine defaults.

5. CONDITION OBJECT
Used for gating, branching, and logic.
Condition {
  key: string (required)
  gte?: number
  lte?: number
  eq?: number | string | boolean
}

Rules
At least one operator must be present.
Conditions must be safe and non‑recursive.

6. NODE UI CONFIG
Optional per‑node visual overrides.
NodeUI {
  backgroundImage: string (optional)
  textColor: string (optional)
  accentColor: string (optional)
  fontFamily: string (optional)
}

Rules
UI config never affects logic.
Missing fields fall back to global defaults.

7. VERSIONING RULES
Every Hunt must declare:
version: "1.0"

Rules
Version increments only when schema changes.
Admin tools must output the correct version.
Game engine must validate version compatibility.

